main event: A witness observed an unidentified object resembling a plane climbing at a 35-degree angle and passing over them at a high rate of speed in Redwood City, California on November 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object made a distinctive sound as it moved., The object appeared to be very bright and had a metallic sheen., The sighting involved visual observations only, with no photos or physical evidence., The conclusion was stated as DASC 55 from FAA Air Traffic Control., Witnesses reported a clear sky during the observation.
sighted object: an unidentified object resembling a plane
witness description: The object was reported to be bright, climbing rapidly, and making a distinctive sound during its flight.
